OL,3,CPolice officers who pepper-sprayed and
OL,4,Ctasered amputee found not guilty
OL,6,F"Use of force must be reasonable,
OL,7,Fnecessary and proportionate and
OL,8,Fofficers know they will be held
OL,9,Faccountable every time.
OL,11,F"The officers in this case have been
OL,12,Fheld accountable to a criminal
OL,13,Fthreshold and we respect the jury's
OL,14,Fdecision.
OL,16,F"While this concludes the criminal
OL,17,Finvestigation, both officers will now
OL,18,Fface gross misconduct proceedings."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUxD@AOUzD@cO]
