OL,4,Ctasered amputee found not guilty
OL,6,FThe Independent Office for Police
OL,7,FConduct (IOPC) said that both officers
OL,8,Fshould face a gross misconduct hearing
OL,9,Ffor potential breaches of the police
OL,10,Fstandards of professional behaviour
OL,11,Frelating to use of force, and
OL,12,Fauthority, respect and courtesy, with
OL,13,FPc Comotto facing a further misconduct
OL,14,Fallegation relating to comments she
OL,15,Fmade on social media after the
OL,16,Fincident.
OL,18,FThe watchdog said it would liaise with
OL,19,FSussex Police about the misconduct
OL,20,Fhearings now that criminal proceedings
OL,21,Fare over.
