OL,6,FDuring her evidence, Pc Comotto said
OL,7,Fshe believed using the Taser was the
OL,8,Fsafest way to "protect" Mr Burgess as
OL,9,Fshe feared her colleague using the
OL,10,Fbaton again would cause more harm.
OL,12,FShe added she knew from her training
OL,13,Fthe risk of injury to Mr Burgess was
OL,14,Fhigher with a baton than with a Taser.
OL,16,FShe said: "It was proportionate
OL,17,Fbecause other tactics had failed. If I
OL,18,Fdidn't act, something worse could
OL,19,Fhappen."
OL,26,@pD@OOUpD@WO]xD@KOU{D@HO]
